# React / Next.js Patterns

## Server vs Client Components

- Default to Server Components. Only add `"use client"` when the component needs hooks, event handlers, browser APIs, or interactivity.
- Keep client boundaries as low in the tree as possible — wrap only the interactive part, not the whole page.

## Components

- Use functional components only.
- Use named exports for components (not default exports), except for Next.js pages/layouts which require default exports.
- Place custom components in `src/components/`. shadcn/ui components go in `src/components/ui/`.

## Styling

- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional/merged class names:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

<div className={cn("base-classes", isActive && "active-classes")} />
```

- Use Tailwind classes directly. Avoid inline `style` props.

## Next.js Conventions

- Set page metadata via the `metadata` export, not `<Head>`:

```tsx
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "Page Title",
  description: "Page description.",
};
```

- Use `next/image` for all images and `next/link` for internal navigation.
- Colocate loading, error, and not-found states using the App Router file conventions (`loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`).

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible.
- Images require meaningful `alt` text (or `alt=""` for decorative images).
- Use semantic HTML elements (`nav`, `main`, `section`, `article`, `button`) over generic `div`/`span`.
